                            <comment id="252674" author="jgmitter" created="Wed, 7 Aug 2019 16:08:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket remains open to improve the truncation already implemented.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="228534" author="tappro" created="Thu, 24 May 2018 14:23:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;if truncate size is in DoM range then SETATTR is not needed because there will be truncate. I think it is safe to check that on client and decide to send setattr or not&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="228148" author="bzzz" created="Fri, 18 May 2018 16:00:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is not good on its own - two sync RPCs instead of one. but also breaks optimisation in osd_punch() as we can&apos;t skip truncate to existing i_size.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
